# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Book Studio AI — environment variables
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in when you wire up real services.
# The MVP runs fully WITHOUT any of these (client-side persistence + placeholder AI).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Database (Railway Postgres) — used by Drizzle + the Auth.js adapter.
# Use the PUBLIC proxy URL for external connections (Vercel, GitHub Actions CI);
# the `.railway.internal` URL only resolves inside Railway. Code reads
# DATABASE_URL_PUBLIC first, then falls back to DATABASE_URL.
DATABASE_URL_PUBLIC=
DATABASE_URL=

# Auth.js (NextAuth v5) — Google sign-in.
# AUTH_SECRET signs the session JWT: generate with `npx auth secret`.
# Client_ID / Client_Secret are the Google OAuth credentials (non-standard
# names, wired in explicitly in src/auth.ts). Set all three in Vercel
# (Production + Preview). Authorized redirect URI on the Google client:
#   https://<your-domain>/api/auth/callback/google
AUTH_SECRET=
Client_ID=
Client_Secret=

# AI provider — set OPENAI_API_KEY to enable real AI (gpt-4o via the Vercel AI
# SDK). Without it, src/lib/ai/* falls back to deterministic placeholder output.
# Server-side only — do NOT prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Stripe (Phase 5 — Billing & Plan Gating). ALL server-only — never NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# We use Hosted Checkout + the Customer Portal, so no publishable key is needed.
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY     — secret API key (test: sk_test_…, live: sk_live_…).
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET — signing secret for /api/stripe/webhook (whsec_…),
#                           from the Stripe Dashboard webhook endpoint (or the
#                           Stripe CLI `stripe listen` output in test mode).
#   STRIPE_PRICE_ID       — the recurring Price id for the Pro plan (price_…).
# The app is import-safe without these (src/lib/stripe.ts is lazy); a real
# Stripe call is what fails if they're missing.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
STRIPE_PRICE_ID=
